    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Add missing PLMN configuration function implementation\n\n### Summary\nThe `set_plmn_config()` function was declared in the header but never implemented, causing linker errors when modules tried to use it. This fix provides a proper implementation that validates inputs and sets the PLMN fields correctly.\n\nThis resolves issues where gNB configuration would fail during startup with \"undefined reference\" errors.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/GNB_APP/gnb_config.c`: Added `set_plmn_config()` implementation with proper validation\n- `openair2/GNB_APP/gnb_config.h`: Kept existing function declaration\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Build OAI5G with gNB configuration that references multiple PLMNs\n2. Linker will fail with \"undefined reference to `set_plmn_config`\"\n3. gNB startup will abort with configuration errors\n\nWith this fix, the gNB should start normally and handle PLMN configuration without errors.\n"
}